# shadcn/ui (Base UI based)

## ⚠️ This is Base UI, not Radix — compose with the `render` prop, NOT `asChild`
The shadcn components here wrap `@base-ui/react`. To render a primitive *as* another element
(e.g. a trigger that looks like a Button, or a Button that is actually a link), pass a
`render` element. **`asChild` does not exist here.**

```tsx
// Button that navigates (button-styled link)
<Button render={<Link href="/appointments" />}>Book Now</Button>

// Dialog/Sheet/Select trigger rendered as a Button
<DialogTrigger render={<Button variant="destructive" size="sm" />}>Delete</DialogTrigger>
<SheetTrigger render={<Button variant="outline" size="icon" aria-label="Open menu" />}>
  <MenuIcon />
</SheetTrigger>
```

## Owning the components
- shadcn is **not** an npm UI dependency — its CLI copied source into `src/components/ui/`.
  You may edit those files directly. Add new primitives with `npx shadcn@latest add <name>`
  (e.g. `tabs`, `accordion`, `avatar`); don't reinvent them by hand.
- Build feature UI by **composing** existing primitives. Available now: `button`, `card`,
  `input`, `label`, `textarea`, `select`, `badge`, `dialog`, `dropdown-menu`, `sheet`,
  `navigation-menu`, `carousel`, `separator`, `skeleton`, `sonner`.

## Usage conventions (match existing code)
- **Button** variants: `default | outline | secondary | ghost | destructive | link`;
  sizes: `default | xs | sm | lg | icon | icon-sm | icon-lg`. Pill buttons add `rounded-full`.
- **Card**: compose `Card` > `CardHeader`/`CardContent`/`CardFooter` with `CardTitle`/`CardDescription`.
- **Badge** for status: drive `variant` from a `Record<Status, "default"|"secondary"|"destructive"|"outline">` map.
- **Dialog** to confirm destructive actions (e.g. delete); **Sheet** for the mobile nav drawer.
- **Carousel** (Embla) for sliders: `opts={{ align, loop }}`, `plugins={[Autoplay({...})]}`,
  `CarouselItem` widths via `basis-*` (`md:basis-1/2 lg:basis-1/3`).
- **Icons**: `lucide-react`, sized with `size-4` etc. Merge classes with `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`;
  define new variant sets with `cva`.
